    ],
    "claim": "`invalidateReward()` can be called on any tracked reward token, including `redemptionWriteOff`. Once that slot is invalidated, redemptions still mint write-off tokens, but `_checkpoint()` skips the token entirely, so `_syncUserRedemptions()` never deducts redeemed collateral from borrower balances. If the token is revived later, the backlog is redistributed using the then-current borrow-share distribution instead of the historical one.",
    "impact": "Borrowers can keep borrowing against collateral that has already been redeemed away, avoid liquidations they should have faced, or withdraw more collateral than the pair still owns. If the token is later revived, the missed write-offs can be charged to the wrong borrowers, socializing losses onto later debt holders.",
    "paths": [
      "Reward manager invalidates `redemptionWriteOff`.",
      "A redemption occurs and `redeemCollateral()` mints additional write-off supply.",
      "Borrowers call `borrow()`, `removeCollateral()`, `repayWithCollateral()`, or get liquidated; `_syncUserRedemptions()` sees no new `claimable_reward[address(redemptionWriteOff)]`, so collateral stays overstated.",
      "Optionally, the token is revived later and the entire missed backlog is applied against the current share distribution instead of the historical one."
    ]
